  "name": "Morrison VAD Hemolysis CFD — Minimal Profile Credibility Package",
  "description": "This package documents credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to support pump design decisions for Class III devices. Turbulence-induced shear stress fields are resolved using a k-omega SST formulation; hemolysis index is computed via a power-law damage accumulation model. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation was performed across key blood rheology parameters. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated under ASME V&V 40-2018 at Model Risk Level 5; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved levels below required thresholds, driving a Not Accepted determination in the underlying COU assessment. This minimal-profile package aggregates the credibility evidence for downstream audit purposes and records the final accepted disposition of the submission package itself.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cfd-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-bench-validation-2022"
  ],
