      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with regression test suite covering at least 90% of active code paths; formal release documentation and change logs maintained.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is under version control and a partial regression suite exists; however, code coverage falls below the 90% threshold required at MRL 5 and formal release documentation is incomplete. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations with demonstrated order-of-accuracy recovery to within 5% of theoretical rate.",
      "rationale": "MMS was applied to the Navier-Stokes equations but not to the hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. Order-of-accuracy recovery was demonstrated for momentum equations only. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) reported for all quantities of interest with GCI below 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed; GCI for hemolysis index on the fine mesh was 18%, exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. Spatial discretization error remains a dominant uncertainty source. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions match VAD operating envelope within documented uncertainty bounds; fluid properties, rotational speed, and flow rate replicate clinical use conditions.",
      "rationale": "Bench validation experiments used bovine blood at 37°C and matched target flow rate; however, rotational speed was limited to 2400 RPM versus the 3200 RPM clinical operating point. Partial condition coverage achieved. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric u_val) computed with combined experimental and numerical uncertainty; model prediction within two combined standard uncertainties of measured value.",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index exceeded measured values by 34% at the primary operating point; combined uncertainty budget does not account for the discrepancy. Validation metric u_val was computed but threshold was not met. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted quantities of interest (hemolysis index, normalized index of hemolysis) directly correspond to regulatory submission metrics and clinical risk endpoints.",
      "rationale": "The model outputs hemolysis index which maps to normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used in regulatory submissions; however, the mapping function introduces additional model-form uncertainty not quantified in this assessment. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the full range of COU operating conditions including device geometry, flow regime, and patient population variability; validation hierarchy spans unit, subsystem, and system levels.",
